               <name xml:id="tag14" type="person">
          Buffon
        </name>
            </rs> could supply the want of<lb/>
and extended system of experimental<lb/>
Knowledge.<lb/>
And it was not till chemical<lb/>
analysis had discovered the real composition<lb/>
And it was not till chemical<lb/>
an extended system of experimental<lb/>
analysis had discovered the real composition<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="13"
                xml:id="pb-13"
                facs="#i13"/>
            <lb/>
of mineral bodies and given accuracy<lb/>
to the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">systems</hi> of Classification,<lb/>
It was not till this period that the<lb/>
changes taking place in the surface of<lb/>
the Globe in the present time could<lb/>
be accurately ascertained or any true<lb/>
analogical evidences gained of the<lb/>
intimate nature of the revolutions which<lb/>
had occurred in past ages.-<lb/>
One of the first persons who endeavored<lb/>
to employ real mineralogical and chemical<lb/>
knowledge in the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">solution</hi> of the most<lb/>
remarkable appearances of the surface of the<lb/>
Globe was the late <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag15"
