            <lb/>
similar to that which actuated those<lb/>
celebrated men: and his labours though<lb/>
directed toward objects much more obscure<lb/>
and more difficultly attainable have<lb/>
have been highly meritorious and<lb/>
productive of important results.-<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="15"
                xml:id="pb-15"
                facs="#i15"/>
            <lb/>
Whitehurst passed the early part of his life<lb/>
in <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag20"
                ref="#place_085"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag20" type="place">
          Derbyshire
        </name>
            </rs>.<lb/>
And it was from an observation of the<lb/>
many interesting phenomena of the<lb/>
mineral kingdom which occur upon a<lb/>
great scale in that County that he was<lb/>
first induced to direct his attention to<lb/>
Geology not so much as He himself informs<lb/>
us with a view of constructing a Theory<lb/>
as with the hope of obtaining such<lb/>
a competent knowledge of subterraneous<lb/>
Geography as might be applicable to<lb/>
useful purpose and to discoveries in<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">Mining</hi> -<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="16"
                xml:id="pb-16"
                facs="#i16"/>
            <lb/>
His attention was however soon arested<lb/>
by a fact which it was scarcely<lb/>
possible for an active mind to notice<lb/>
without indulging in speculation<lb/>
without reasoning from effects concerning<lb/>
causes.-<lb/>
The principal strata in <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag21"
                ref="#place_085"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag21" type="place">
          Derbyshire
        </name>
            </rs> are<lb/>
            <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
