                 rend="strikethrough">Sections</del>
            <lb/>
Sketches of the sections of the strata will<lb/>
perhaps illustrate the History and a single<lb/>
glance of the eye will be more convincing<lb/>
than the most minute description -<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">Instances</hi>
            <lb/>
It was in examining this curious<lb/>
phaenomena that Whitehurst was led<lb/>
to form the conclusion of the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">connection</hi> of<lb/>
the disorder of the strata with the<lb/>
presence of <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">the <rs xml:id="ttag26" ref="#misc_855" type="miscellaneous">
                  <term xml:id="tag26">
          toadstone
        </term>
               </rs>
            </hi> and finding<lb/>
that this rock was lower than the others<lb/>
and that no metalic veins existed in it<lb/>
and that even the veins of the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag27"
                ref="#chemical_090"
                type="chemical">
               <term xml:id="tag27">
          Limestone
          
        </term>
            </rs>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="18"
                xml:id="pb-18"
                facs="#i18"/>
            <lb/>
when intersected by it appeared on the<lb/>
opposite <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">sides</hi> -<lb/>
He concluded that the strata were of<lb/>
prior formation and that this <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">substance</hi>
            <lb/>
had been interfused amongst them in<lb/>
a liquid state by some great convulsion<lb/>
of Nature. which had produced <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">chasms</del>
            <lb/>
chasms capable of receiving it and<lb/>
which had broken and dislodged the<lb/>
