            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="22"
                xml:id="pb-22"
                facs="#i22"/>
            <lb/>
And from so great a change in the surface<lb/>
the Author conceives that an alteration in<lb/>
the centre of gravity of the earth must<lb/>
have occurred and that in consequence<lb/>
at this period its axis may have gained<lb/>
its present inclination to the plane of<lb/>
its orbit.<lb/>
Such appear to have been the progress<lb/>
of the Mind of the philosopher of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag36"
                ref="#place_492"
